results.name: Number of acute integer triangles with perimeter n and relatively prime side lengths.
example: For n=10 there are A005044(10) = 2 integer triangles: [2,4,4] and [3,3,4]; both are acute, but GCD(2,4,4)>1, therefore a(9) = 1.
results.author: _Reinhard Zumkeller_, May 05 2002
